review_blob: Well bud is by far the average mans beer.  Average taste, easy drinking, its good for a day of watching football or going out to a sports bar.
My favorite of the malt liquors.  I can actually stand the taste of it when its not almost frozen like other malt liquors.
Well not really being a high gravity fan I was quite surprised with the taste, but for the alcohol content you cannot do much better, at least for the money
Golden Yellow, gotta have the lime, at least for the first one, but after that let it slide to much citric acid.  Funny, but i liked this beer a lot more when i was in high school.
This was a little disappointing because i was really looking forward to trying this beer, but overall it was average, by no means great.
More of a classic lager as opposed to guinness and the flavor is quite a contrast too.  Nice for drinking with a meal or all by itself.
Really impressive.  Pilsener fans try this beer, and i tell you that you will enjoy it.  Golden, smooth, and great flavor I thoroughly  enjoyed it
The aussies know what theyre doing.  A crisp golden beer with a mild, yet pleasing flavor.  Give it a try to break the monatony of everyday beer.
I was really excited for this beer since barley creek has some high quality beers, but the extra hops were just too much for me, an extremely dry tasting beer.
Overall a good beer I like the flavor, and I like the aroma and appearance.  I could drink this almost every night of the week and I usually do.
The flavor turned me off right away.  Not much of a head and not much for the smell either.  I was disappointed.
This is somewhat like labatt blue in flavor and it does contain a higher alcohol content.  Smooth taste, nice aroma, it does the job if you need something to drink.
This is one of my favorite overall beers, I simply like the smooth taste and finish.  No bitterness to deal with, and on tap is definitely the way to go.
